    • isDateInRange

      public static boolean isDateInRange​(DateUtils.DateStructure testableDate, DateUtils.DateStructure fromDate, DateUtils.DateStructure toDate, boolean including)
      Checks if given date testableDate is in range of dates, starting from fromDate ending ending with toDate. Including both if including is true.
      Parameters:
      testableDate - Testable date.
      fromDate - Date from which range starts.
      toDate - Date with which range ends.
      including - If true, start and end will be [including], else both are (excluding).
      Returns:
      True if testableDate is in range from fromDate to toDate.

    • isDateInRange

      public static boolean isDateInRange​(DateUtils.DateStructure testableDate, DateUtils.DateStructure fromDate, DateUtils.DateStructure toDate, boolean fromIncluding, boolean toIncluding)
      Checks if given date testableDate is in range of dates, starting from fromDate ending ending with toDate. Including fromDate if fromIncluding is true. Including toDate if toIncluding is true.
      Parameters:
      testableDate - Testable date.
      fromDate - Date from which range starts.
      toDate - Date with which range ends.
      fromIncluding - If true, fromDate will be [inclusive], else (exclusive).
      toIncluding - If true, toDate will be [inclusive], else (exclusive).
      Returns:
      True if testableDate is in range from fromDate to toDate.
